Patient Management & Visualisation Tool

Description

A patient management tool to visualise scans & manage patient data. An entry for the Dot Plot x Tech Academia accelerator programme

Table of Contents

Installation
Usage
Contributing
License
Installation

Prerequisites

Ensure you have Python installed (preferably version 3.7 or higher).
Ensure you have Pipenv installed.
Ensure you have Node.js installed (preferably version 14 or higher).
Ensure you have npm installed.
Clone the Repository

Open your terminal.

Clone the repository by running the following command:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
Navigate to the project directory:

cd front-end
When dealing with the front-end

cd back-end
When dealing with the back-end

& to run files, cd into the folder first:

cd folder_name
python folder_name
Set Up the Virtual Environment and Install Dependencies

Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:

pipenv install
Activate the virtual environment:

pipenv shell
Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root directory of the project.

Add the necessary environment variables to the .env file. Example:

PORT_NUMBER=3000
DATABASE_URL=
CONNECTION_STRING=
Usage

Running the Application

Ensure you are in the virtual environment. If not, activate it:

pipenv shell
Run the application:

python path/to/folder/name.py
or cd to the folder of the file.

Additional Commands

To run database migrations, use:

python app/core/db_initialiser.py
this isn't needed though.

Contributing

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch (git checkout -b feature-branch).
Make your changes.
Commit your changes (git commit -m 'Add some feature').
Push to the branch (git push origin feature-branch).
Open a pull request.
